The new logformat configuration files enable flexible log outputs that can be easily
customised and formatted in various ways.

At the top of the file are a number of directives which affect the format.

#format:"format"  - format may be:-
                    'csv' - comma separated values
                    'tsv' - tab separated values
                    'ssv' - space separated values
                    default is 'tsv'
                    other formats may be added in the future

#add_header:      - if present a header line of labels will be output at startup (to emulate full csv format)

#add_quotes_to_strings:   - if present adds quotes round string fields

#use_dash_for_blanks:     - replace any blank strings with '-' for easier readability

Then add fields you require, in the format below, and in the order required:-

    [label.]field[:parameter]

    where
       label = your choice of label - this will be output in any header - only A-Z, a-z and 0-9 will be used
          if absent defaults to field.
       field = one of the fields defined below
       parameter - only ReqHeader and ResHeader require parameters

Fields available:-

Blank		        Empty column
ActionWord      	ActionWord(s) (*DENIED*, *EXCEPTION, etc)
AuthRoute		    How this has been authenticated (auth_method:how_selected)
BodySize 		    Size of body in bytes
Category		    Category(ises)
ClientHost		    Client hostname (from reverse DNS)
ClientHostOrIP 		ClientHost, or if unavailable the ClientIP
ClientIP 		    Client IP
DurationMs 		    Time taken to service request in ms
EndLtime 		    End timestamp local time in human-readable format
EndUtime 		    End timestamp in utime format
ExtFlags 		    Extended Flags = ListenPort:ProxyServce:AuthRoute (see notes/New_log_fields_in_logformat7-8.pdf)
GroupName 		    Filter group Name
GroupNo 		    Filter group Number
ListenPort 		    E2g port that accepted the connection
LogId1  		    As defined in e2guardian.conf
LogId2  		    As defined in e2guardian.conf
MessageNo 		    e2g Message Number
MimeType 		    Mime type
Naughtiness 		Naughtiness score
ProductId  		    As defined in e2guardian.conf
ProxyIP 		    Upstream proxy IP if used
ProxyService		Type of e2g service flags
                        1st character - T= transparent, P= explict proxy or I= ICAP
                        2nd character - H= HTTP, S= HTTPS or CONNECT, or M= MITM (http request inside https connection)
ReqHeader:param     Request header of param type
ResHeader:param 	Response header of param type
ReqType 		    request type ('GET','PUT','POST' etc)
RequestId 		    unique request ID (= ThreadId + StartUtime)
ResCode      		HTML Response Code
SearchTerms 		Detected Search Terms
Server			    Server name
StartLtime 		    Start timestamp local time in human-readable format
StartUtime 		    Start timestamp unix time in secs since 1/1/1970
ThreadId		    Thread_id of the worker logging this request/response
Url 			    Url of request
User 			    User name
UserAgent 		    UserAgent in request
WhatsNaughty		What is naughty
WhatCombi 		    ActionWord(s) + WhatsNaughty

See examples in configs/log_formats